---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="ABOUT // AOI_LABS">
  <main class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <section class="mb-20">
      <span class="font-headline text-[#e4f700] tracking-[0.3em] text-[10px] uppercase mb-4 block">Personal_Dossier</span>
      <h1 class="font-headline text-4xl md:text-6xl font-black uppercase leading-[0.9] mb-8">
        A celebration <br/> of the <span class="text-[#e4f700]">harmony</span> between humans and AI.
      </h1>
      <div class="aspect-video bg-white/5 border border-white/10 flex items-center justify-center mb-8 relative group overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-tr from-[#e4f700]/5 to-transparent opacity-50"></div>
        <span class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest opacity-30 italic z-10">[ Insert: Photo of Work Desk or Robot Assembly ]</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 mb-32">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold uppercase sticky top-24">The Vision</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-6 text-[#ababab] leading-relaxed text-lg font-light">
        <p class="text-white font-headline font-bold text-xl leading-tight tracking-tight mb-4">
          Synthesizing Physical Action with Autonomous Intelligence.
        </p>
        <p>
          I believe that the convergence of AI and robotics transforms machines from mere industrial tools into proactive life partners. While a robot provides the physical "body" to act, AI provides the "mind" to reason. By integrating these two, we create an entity capable of independent judgment and meaningful interaction—a presence that can evolve into a true companion.
        </p>
        <p>
          Unlike traditional automation, an AI-driven robot possesses the fluidity to adapt to unexpected situations. Imagine a robotic companion that functions as a loyal pet, yet seamlessly transitions into a technical assistant when you need support, or a first responder during an emergency. My mission is to engineer this "flexible agency," building a future where technology doesn't just serve humans, but truly understands and co-exists with them.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-12 border-t border-white/10 pt-20">
      <div class="md:col-span-4">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold uppercase">Core Philosophy</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-8 grid grid-cols-1 gap-12">
       
        <div class="glass-card p-8 border-l-2 border-[#e4f700] flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div>
            <span class="font-headline text-[10px] text-[#e4f700] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-1 block">Philosophy_01</span>
            <h3 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold uppercase text-white">USER-CENTRIC DESIGN SYNTHESIS</h3>
            <h4 class="font-headline text-sm text-[#e4f700] tracking-widest uppercase mt-1">Prioritizing Intuition and Purposeful Engineering</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-[#ababab] leading-relaxed font-light">
            I design from the user’s perspective, ensuring that every feature serves a clear purpose. While novelty and technical sophistication matter, my priority is delivering exactly what is needed—no more, no less. This requires translating user behavior and edge cases into concrete engineering decisions, creating systems that feel natural and intuitive because they were deliberately built that way.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="glass-card p-8 border-l-2 border-[#00eefc] flex flex-col gap-4">
          <div>
            <span class="font-headline text-[10px] text-[#00eefc] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-1 block">Philosophy_02</span>
            <h3 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold uppercase text-white">EVOLUTIONARY DEVELOPMENT & LOGGING</h3>
            <h4 class="font-headline text-sm text-[#00eefc] tracking-widest uppercase mt-1">Iterating Through Real-World Feedback</h4>
          </div>
          <p class="text-base text-[#ababab] leading-relaxed font-light">
            I believe that a product is never truly finished, but continuously evolving. Whether developing AI robots or utility applications, I embrace a Version 1.0 mindset—launching core functionality first, then iteratively refining it through real-world use. I document this process in my System Log, treating each technical challenge and user insight as a driver for the next iteration.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
